2447:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           How to use this low power mode:
2448:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - It is not recommended to use with interruption or DMA
2449:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             since these modes have to clear immediately the EOC flag
2450:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             (by CPU to free the IRQ pending event or by DMA).
2451:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             Auto wait will work but fort a very short time, discarding
2452:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             its intended benefit (except specific case of high load of CPU
2453:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             or DMA transfers which can justify usage of auto wait).
2454:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - Do use with polling: 1. Start conversion,
2455:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             2. Later on, when conversion data is needed: poll for end of
2456:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             conversion  to ensure that conversion is completed and
2457:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             retrieve ADC conversion data. This will trig another
2458:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             ADC conversion start.
2459:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - ADC low power mode "auto power-off" (feature available on
2460:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           this device if parameter LL_ADC_LP_AUTOPOWEROFF is available):
2461:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           the ADC automatically powers-off after a conversion and
2462:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           automatically wakes up when a new conversion is triggered
2463:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           (with startup time between trigger and start of sampling).
2464:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           This feature can be combined with low power mode "auto wait".
2465:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   With ADC low power mode "auto wait", the ADC conversion data read
2466:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         is corresponding to previous ADC conversion start, independently
2467:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         of delay during which ADC was idle.
2468:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         Therefore, the ADC conversion data may be outdated: does not
2469:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         correspond to the current voltage level on the selected
2470:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         ADC channel.
2471:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @rmtoll CFGR1    WAIT           LL_ADC_GetLowPowerMode\n
2472:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         CFGR1    AUTOFF         LL_ADC_GetLowPowerMode
2473:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @param  ADCx ADC instance
2474:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @retval Returned value can be one of the following values:
2475:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_ADC_LP_MODE_NONE
2476:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_ADC_LP_AUTOWAIT
2477:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_ADC_LP_AUTOPOWEROFF
2478:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_ADC_LP_AUTOWAIT_AUTOPOWEROFF
2479:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   */
2480:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h **** __STATIC_INLINE uint32_t LL_ADC_GetLowPowerMode(const ADC_TypeDef *ADCx)
