4144:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h **** /**
4145:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @brief  Set ADC analog watchdog thresholds value of both thresholds
4146:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         high and low.
4147:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   If value of only one threshold high or low must be set,
4148:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         use function @ref LL_ADC_SetAnalogWDThresholds().
4149:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   In case of ADC resolution different of 12 bits,
4150:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         analog watchdog thresholds data require a specific shift.
4151:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         Use helper macro @ref __LL_ADC_ANALOGWD_SET_THRESHOLD_RESOLUTION().
4152:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   On this STM32 series, there are 2 kinds of analog watchdog
4153:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         instance:
4154:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - AWD standard (instance AWD1):
4155:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - channels monitored: can monitor 1 channel or all channels.
4156:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - groups monitored: ADC group regular.
4157:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - resolution: resolution is not limited (corresponds to
4158:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             ADC resolution configured).
4159:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - AWD flexible (instances AWD2, AWD3):
4160:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - channels monitored: flexible on channels monitored, selection is
4161:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             channel wise, from from 1 to all channels.
4162:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             Specificity of this analog watchdog: Multiple channels can
4163:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             be selected. For example:
4164:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             (LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNEL4_REG_INJ | LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNEL5_REG_INJ | ...)
4165:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - groups monitored: not selection possible (monitoring on both
4166:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             groups regular and injected).
4167:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             Channels selected are monitored on groups regular and injected:
4168:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNELxx_REG_INJ (do not use parameters
4169:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNELxx_REG and LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNELxx_INJ)
4170:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - resolution: resolution is not limited (corresponds to
4171:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             ADC resolution configured).
4172:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   If ADC oversampling is enabled, ADC analog watchdog thresholds are
4173:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         impacted: the comparison of analog watchdog thresholds is done on
4174:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         oversampling final computation (after ratio and shift application):
4175:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         ADC data register bitfield [15:4] (12 most significant bits).
4176:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         Examples:
4177:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - Oversampling ratio and shift selected to have ADC conversion data
4178:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           on 12 bits (ratio 16 and shift 4, or ratio 32 and shift 5, ...):
4179:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           ADC analog watchdog thresholds must be divided by 16.
4180:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - Oversampling ratio and shift selected to have ADC conversion data
ARM GAS  /tmp/cca1Np6D.s 			page 76


4181:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           on 14 bits (ratio 16 and shift 2, or ratio 32 and shift 3, ...):
4182:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           ADC analog watchdog thresholds must be divided by 4.
4183:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - Oversampling ratio and shift selected to have ADC conversion data
4184:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           on 16 bits (ratio 16 and shift none, or ratio 32 and shift 1, ...):
4185:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           ADC analog watchdog thresholds match directly to ADC data register.
4186:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   On this STM32 series, setting of this feature is conditioned to
4187:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         ADC state:
4188:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         ADC must be disabled or enabled without conversion on going
4189:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         on group regular.
4190:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @rmtoll AWD1TR   HT1            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds\n
4191:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         AWD2TR   HT2            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds\n
4192:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         AWD3TR   HT3            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds\n
4193:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         AWD1TR   LT1            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds\n
4194:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         AWD2TR   LT2            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds\n
4195:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         AWD3TR   LT3            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds
4196:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @param  ADCx ADC instance
4197:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @param  AWDy This parameter can be one of the following values:
4198:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_ADC_AWD1
4199:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_ADC_AWD2
4200:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_ADC_AWD3
4201:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @param  AWDThresholdHighValue Value between Min_Data=0x000 and Max_Data=0xFFF
4202:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @param  AWDThresholdLowValue Value between Min_Data=0x000 and Max_Data=0xFFF
